        "content": "<p>E-commerce impacts and is impacted by many enterprise departments which have their own KPIs, budgets, decision making rules and ambitions: sales, marketing, IT, finances, logistics, buyers, security, HR, legal etc. Big changes (like implementing e-commerce solution or significant changes in business processes) usually take a lot of energy and be very continuous.</p>\n\n<p>Regional variability creates an additional challenge on top of the organizational complexity. Additional regions may give additional stakeholders, and the local specific creates additional complexity by itself. Local specific matters in taxation (which may impact pricing), legal requirements and practices, HR specific, cultural differences.</p>\n\n<p>The complexity of the enterprise IT is explained by the previous IT growth and acquiring other companies. It results with extreme complexity of the IT infrastructure: it consists of a mix of super-actual software (like AI services), very old legacy systems, software inherited from acquired companies, big variety of local and industry specific software (like bookkeeping, legal, ERPs etc).&nbsp;</p>\n",
