        "content": "<p>Enterprises needs to keep speed and flexibility to stay a leader on the market. However, the organizational complexity makes changes (like implementing e-commerce solution or significant changes of business processes) very expensive in terms of time and efforts.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>It takes a lot of energy to run a project and it is used to be very continuous. When projects size grows linear, then efforts, risks and continuity grow exponentially.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>An effort to resolve the regional complexity by designing and implementing by one time a unified solution which covers all or most of all of regions leads to creation of a &ldquo;monster&rdquo; which is very expensive to change, very expensive to maintain and which cannot be easily replaced when it becomes a problem (what happens quite soon after launch).&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>The IT complexity restricts business transformation and may be a threat to the market leadership. It should be approached somehow; it is required to work out the method of constant complexity reduction and painless legacy substitution.</p>\n",
